{
  "texts": [
    "Backward Continuity ensures the model doesn't forget or contradict information from the prompt.",
    "Forward Continuity.",
    "This criterion assesses whether generated responses proceed naturally and consistently from the given context (e.g., look at whether the model can generate responses that align with the provided context and develop and expand on it to reflect human thought processes) [4].",
    "This might include, for example, elaborating on certain beliefs, providing examples, or making connections between different ideas).",
    "It asserts that samples from P(response|prompt) make sense i.e."
  ]
}